result.execSummary:
The defendant Jill L Winters was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse, Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: If probation becomes revoked, no sentence credit per agreement of counsel and order of the court, as credit was applied to 2014CT106.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.

Defendant will enter a plea of NO CONTEST.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty to 14CT106 - OWI - 3rd and will dismiss count 2; DRI 14CM237; 2015CM6 count 1 and 2015CM25 count 1 and the balance of the counts are to be dismissed and read-in.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  DA confirms compliance with victim witness rights.  Sentencing statement by DA.  Sentencing statement by Atty Selsing.  Statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to:

2014CT106 (OWI - 3rd)
- 50 days county jail to commence immediately and with huber.
-$650 fine plus court costs
-D.L. revocation for 27 months
-IID for 27 months
-Blood draw fee - $42.50
-AODA

2015CM6 (Ct 1-Battery-Dom) & 2015CM25 (Ct 1-BJ)

Sentence Withheld and places the defendant on probation for a period of 2 years.

Court costs
Complete the AODA that was ordered under the OWI - 3rd offense.
Defendant is to maintain absolute sobriety - not to possess or consume any alcohol, illegal drugs or prescription drugs without a valid prescription.
Defendant is not to be on any premises that is licensed to sell alcohol by the drink.  No bars, taverns or restaurant.
